<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="501" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[845,1483,1482,1534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">
Biology.—Aspects of the growth of this species were characterized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Boos Jr., H. &amp; D. Silva-Castiglioni &amp; K. Schacht &amp; L. Buckup &amp; G. Bond- Buckup" box="[1032,1233,1511,1534]" journalOrPublisher="Revista Brasileira de Zoologia" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" pagination="490 - 496" part="23" refId="ref5237" refString="Boos Jr., H., D. Silva-Castiglioni, K. Schacht, L. Buckup, and G. Bond- Buckup. 2006. Crescimento de Aegla jarai Bond-Buckup and Buckup (Crustacea, Anomura, Aeglidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia 23: 490 - 496." title="Crescimento de Aegla jarai Bond-Buckup and Buckup (Crustacea, Anomura, Aeglidae)" type="journal article" year="2006">Boos et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="501" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[845,1483,1560,1730]" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">
Remarks.—The phylogeny of the aeglids shows that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bond-Buckup and Buckup" authorityYear="1994" class="Malacostraca" family="Aeglidae" genus="Aegla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jarai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">A. jarai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to Clade C, with an estimated divergence time of 33.2 ± 1.8 MYA 
<bibRefCitation author="Perez-Losada, M. &amp; G. Bond-Buckup &amp; C. G. Jara &amp; K. A. Crandall" box="[1135,1428,1619,1642]" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" pagination="767 - 780" part="53" refId="ref5388" refString="Perez-Losada, M., G. Bond-Buckup, C. G. Jara, and K. A. Crandall. 2004. Molecular systematics and biogeography of the southern South American fresh-water '' crabs '' Aegla (Decapoda: Anomura: Aeglidae) using multiple heuristic tree search approaches. Systematic Biology 53: 767 - 780." title="Molecular systematics and biogeography of the southern South American fresh-water '' crabs '' Aegla (Decapoda: Anomura: Aeglidae) using multiple heuristic tree search approaches" type="journal article" year="2004">Pérez-Losada et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. The several populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bond-Buckup and Buckup" authorityYear="1994" box="[1106,1193,1648,1671]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aeglidae" genus="Aegla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jarai">
<emphasis box="[1106,1193,1648,1671]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="501">A. jarai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form a nonmonophyletic group, according to these authors, indicating that new systematic studies on this species are needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
